Trim and halve the @green beans{150%grams}.

Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed), then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Slice widthways into pieces about 1/2 cm thick.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans and carrot. Stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of @water{1%splash}, then cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}) and allow to cook until tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Remove the veg and place in a #medium bowl{}. Cover to keep warm.

Wipe out your frying pan, then pop back on frying pan on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%grams}. Fry until the mince has browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another large frying pan on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @vegetable gyozas{10} and fry until golden on the bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once golden, remove from the heat, then add @water{1%tbsp} to the pan. Pop back on medium-low heat and immediately cover with a lid or some foil. Cook until the gyozas are piping hot, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Once the mince is cooked, add the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @hoisin sauce{64%grams}, @ketjap manis{25%grams} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce.

> See pantry for water amount.

Simmer the sauce until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @udon noodles{220%grams} to the pan along with the green beans and carrot.

Toss to coat in the sauce, using a #fork{} to gently separate them. Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of @?water{} if the sauce is too thick.

Share the noodles between your #serving bowls{}.

Top with the veggie gyoza. Enjoy!